Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_bump_grid(25.10)                                create_bump_grid(25.10)

Name
       create_bump_grid - Creates a bump grid

Syntax
        create_bump_grid

       [-help]

       -grid_name <string>

       -layers <string>

       -origin {<x y>}

       -pitch {<x y>}

       Creates a bump grid. A bump grid is a grid for bump/TSV placement  that
       helps in guiding bump placement and bump alignment.

       Note:

              * When  you use the savePartition command, the tool recalculates
                the offset so that a bump can be aligned after assemble.

              * The saveFPlan command saves the   bump  grid  definition  into
                *.fp file.

              * The  loadFPlan  command loads the bump grid file while reading
                the design.

Parameters
       -grid_name <string>
              Specifies the bump grid name.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each create_bump_grid parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_bump_grid

       -layers <string>
              Specifies  the layer names. You can specify the layer of a rela-
              tive bump pin for this option.

              Data_type: string required

       -origin {<x y>}
              Specifies the coordinates of the origin of the bump grid.

              Data_type: point, required

       -pitch {<x y>}
              Specifies the spacing between two bumps. The first value (x) de-
              fines the horizontal spacing and the second  value  (y)  defines
              the vertical spacing.

              Data_type: point, required

Example
              * The  following  command  creates  a  bump  grid  named myGrid-
                Front_9x9:

                create_bump_grid -grid_name myGridFront_9x9 -layers {UBM UBM1}
                -origin {50 50} -pitch {9 9}

